May be an illustration of one or more people and text that says 'CODEPENDENCY CAN LOOK LIKE: -putting someone else's needs above your own -losing yourself in elationships -pleasing others for approval -having trouble setting boundaries -excessively worrying about others -trouble trusting yourself struggling with self doubt @letstalk.mentalhealth'.

node.text: Codependency is an emotional and behavioral condition that affects an individual's ability to have a healthy, mutually satisfying relationship. It is also known as “relationship addiction” because people with codependency often form or maintain relationships that are one-sided, emotionally destructive and/or abusive 🗣🔥

May be an image of text that says 'MORE CONSIDERATE TEXTING "K" "Ok sounds good" "We need to talk." Just let me know what's up please ALL CAPS (when you don't have intimacy) Please use this only when necessary @letstalk.mentalhealth Ghosting someone Letting them know you aren't interested Expecting a reply right away Let's remember people have lives to live.'.

node.text:
What are some other potentially anxiety driving texts? 

These reframes really apply to people that we might not have intimacy to send the top versions to. They obviously don’t apply to every situation, but generally they can be a more considerate way to communicate via text 🗣🔥

node.text:

Original design inspiration from @sa.liine

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Lets Talk Mental Health in London, United Kingdom with @letstalk.mentalhealth. May be an image of text that says 'LIFE Perception Reality Happiness leads to gratitude Success is about achievement Gratitude leads to happiness Success is about self-growth The quality of relationships is measured by their length The quality of relationships is measured by their depth How people treat you is reflection of you How people treat you is reflection of them After trauma, we find peace through understanding After trauma, we often find peace through acceptance Eventually, we "find" ourselves Over time, we create ourselves @letstalk.mentalhealth'.

node.text:
Which one of these hits home for you? 

“Finding myself” has always been kind of a funny term to me - because I’m not lost! I am evolving into the person I currently am. Constantly 🗣🔥

Art by @jcomstock7

node.text: Invalidation is the process of denying, rejecting or dismissing someone's feelings. Invalidation sends the message that a person's subjective emotional experience is inaccurate, insignificant, and/or unacceptable 🗣🔥
